Intake Module

The intake module is the constitutional entry boundary of Posta.

It is where:

External input becomes structured truth.

Authority begins.

Culture is interpreted.

Ledger causality is initiated.

Intake is not “input handling.”

It is transformation from external ambiguity into internal governance.

Domain Responsibilities

This module owns:

Ledger authority infrastructure

Localization and cultural normalization

Structured envelope construction

Authority validation boundary

It does NOT:

Decide policy

Mutate lifecycle

Execute business logic

Perform routing

Enforce capabilities

It prepares truth.
Other modules act on it.

1. Ledger Infrastructure (Constitutional Authority)

The ledger system lives inside intake because:

Authority begins at ingestion.

If intake is corrupted, governance collapses.

The ledger enforces:

Cryptographic immutability

Authority hierarchy validation

Supersession rules

Deterministic ordering

Replay-safe payload evolution

All domain modules commit through:

commitLedgerEvent()

Never bypass it.

LedgerService is sovereign core.
Everything else is projection.

2. Authority Envelope (Versioned Payload Layer)

File:
authorityEnvelope.ts

All payloads must be wrapped in:

{
envelopeVersion: 1,
domain: "...",
event: "...",
data: {...}
}

This ensures:

Schema evolution without DB migration

Replay durability

Versioned institutional memory

Backward compatibility across years

eventType classifies.
envelopeVersion governs payload structure.

Never write raw payload directly again.

3. Authority Hierarchy

Authority is derived, not stored.

Levels:

SYSTEM_AUTOMATED

HUMAN_VERIFIER

HUMAN_ADMIN

EXECUTIVE_OVERRIDE

Supersession rules prevent:

Privilege downgrade override

SYSTEM overriding HUMAN

Equal authority silent takeover

This prevents governance corruption under concurrency.

AuthorityProof conventions enable elevation without schema change.

4. Localization Service

File:
localization.service.ts

This is epistemic intake normalization.

It performs:

Language detection

Dialect identification

Cultural tone neutralization

Translation necessity flagging

It transforms human context into structured interpretation.

It does NOT:

Change meaning

Infer intent

Alter policy outcome

It prepares message for neutral processing.

Cultural Detection

detectCulture():

Returns:

detectedLanguage

confidence

regionalDialect

requiresTranslation

Current logic is simple and demonstrative.

Production recommendation:

Google Cloud Translation API

FastText offline models

Deterministic local language models

Detection must remain:

Stateless.
Deterministic.
Privacy-aware.

Cultural Neutralization

neutralizeAndTranslate():

Transforms regional idioms into neutral professional tone.

Example:

"I no get kobo"
→ "I am currently without funds"

This is not censorship.

It is structural tone stabilization.

Why?

Because downstream systems require:

Intent clarity

Tone neutrality

Non-adversarial language

Governance-safe semantics

Cultural respect means understanding.
Neutralization means structural fairness.

Design Philosophy

Intake is epistemic boundary.

Outside world is messy:

Mixed dialects

Emotional tone

Ambiguous language

Regional slang

Adversarial attempts

Inside system must be:

Deterministic

Structured

Authority-safe

Replay-stable

Localization + Ledger together enforce that boundary.

Failure Philosophy

Localization must never:

Throw fatal errors

Block governance

Leak cultural data

Ledger must:

Fail loudly

Protect authority

Never degrade silently

Intake is split deliberately:

Cultural processing is soft.
Authority processing is hard.

Security Considerations

Localization must not:

Execute scripts

Evaluate embedded HTML

Trust language markers blindly

Ledger must not:

Accept malformed authorityProof

Allow cross-tenant supersession

Allow SYSTEM override escalation

Intake must assume hostile input.

Scalability Considerations

For localization at scale:

Introduce LRU caching for language detection

Introduce async translation queue

Add rate limiting per device

Add observability for dialect frequency

For ledger scale:

Partition by tenant

Archive old commits

Materialize metrics

Add read replicas

What Intake Is Not

It is not:

AI decision engine

Fraud detector

Workflow executor

Business logic layer

It is boundary enforcement.

Determinism

Given same input:

message

device context

authority data

Intake must produce identical structured output.

No randomness.
No hidden mutation.
No time-dependent inference.

Replay must be possible.

Mental Model

Intake is the gate of the republic.

Every external voice enters here.
Every authoritative action begins here.
Every institutional memory commit originates here.

Localization interprets speech.
Ledger records truth.

One softens.
One hardens.

Together they protect institutional integrity.
